<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,762,1615]" pageId="6" pageNumber="401">
Male: Dorsal rim of pygophore concave and slightly furrowed; posterolateral angle not developed (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 11 – 15" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1858,1881]" captionTargetBox="[169,1410,374,1826]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[159,1427,373,1837]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 11 – 15. Paraedessa albomaculata sp. nov. 11 – 13 Male, pygophore; 6 — dorsal view; 7 — posterior view; 8 — ventral view. (Scale = 1 mm). 14 — Paramere, lateral view. (Scale = 0,5 mm). 15 — Female, genital plates. (Scale = 1 mm)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/222978/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="401">
Figs. 
<number pageId="6" pageNumber="401" value="12.0" valueMax="13.0" valueMin="11.0">11– 13</number>
</figureCitation>
). Genital cup processes triangular, long, concave and located lateral to proctiger; apex surpassing the posterior limits of the pygophore (
<figureCitation box="[429,565,1086,1111]" captionStart="FIGURES 11 – 15" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1858,1881]" captionTargetBox="[169,1410,374,1826]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[159,1427,373,1837]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 11 – 15. Paraedessa albomaculata sp. nov. 11 – 13 Male, pygophore; 6 — dorsal view; 7 — posterior view; 8 — ventral view. (Scale = 1 mm). 14 — Paramere, lateral view. (Scale = 0,5 mm). 15 — Female, genital plates. (Scale = 1 mm)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/222978/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="401">
Figs. 
<number box="[493,565,1087,1111]" pageId="6" pageNumber="401" value="12.0" valueMax="13.0" valueMin="11.0">11–13</number>
</figureCitation>
). Parameres flat, narrow; distal margin sloping; anterior expansion digitiform and long, single distal expansion truncate and lateroposteriorly directed (
<figureCitation box="[960,1091,1122,1147]" captionStart="FIGURES 11 – 15" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1858,1881]" captionTargetBox="[169,1410,374,1826]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[159,1427,373,1837]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 11 – 15. Paraedessa albomaculata sp. nov. 11 – 13 Male, pygophore; 6 — dorsal view; 7 — posterior view; 8 — ventral view. (Scale = 1 mm). 14 — Paramere, lateral view. (Scale = 0,5 mm). 15 — Female, genital plates. (Scale = 1 mm)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/222978/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="401">
Figs. 
<number box="[1023,1091,1123,1147]" pageId="6" pageNumber="401" value="12.5" valueMax="14.0" valueMin="11.0">11-14</number>
</figureCitation>
); apex not surpassing posterior limits of pygophore in dorsal view (
<figureCitation box="[562,688,1158,1183]" captionStart="FIGURES 11 – 15" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1858,1881]" captionTargetBox="[169,1410,374,1826]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[159,1427,373,1837]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 11 – 15. Paraedessa albomaculata sp. nov. 11 – 13 Male, pygophore; 6 — dorsal view; 7 — posterior view; 8 — ventral view. (Scale = 1 mm). 14 — Paramere, lateral view. (Scale = 0,5 mm). 15 — Female, genital plates. (Scale = 1 mm)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/222978/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="401">
Fig. 
<number box="[616,688,1159,1183]" pageId="6" pageNumber="401" value="11.5" valueMax="12.0" valueMin="11.0">11–12</number>
</figureCitation>
). Dorsal face of proctiger as long as wide, entire, without a distal shallow concavity. Lateral face of proctiger with slight constriction (
<figureCitation box="[967,1054,1194,1219]" captionStart="FIGURES 11 – 15" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1858,1881]" captionTargetBox="[169,1410,374,1826]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[159,1427,373,1837]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 11 – 15. Paraedessa albomaculata sp. nov. 11 – 13 Male, pygophore; 6 — dorsal view; 7 — posterior view; 8 — ventral view. (Scale = 1 mm). 14 — Paramere, lateral view. (Scale = 0,5 mm). 15 — Female, genital plates. (Scale = 1 mm)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/222978/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="401">
Fig. 
<number box="[1025,1054,1195,1219]" pageId="6" pageNumber="401" value="11.0">11</number>
</figureCitation>
). Lateral expansion of proctiger cordiform, narrow, twice as wide as anal opening, posteriorly curved, projected dorsally beyond above the dorsal face (
<figureCitation box="[213,348,1266,1291]" captionStart="FIGURES 11 – 15" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1858,1881]" captionTargetBox="[169,1410,374,1826]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[159,1427,373,1837]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 11 – 15. Paraedessa albomaculata sp. nov. 11 – 13 Male, pygophore; 6 — dorsal view; 7 — posterior view; 8 — ventral view. (Scale = 1 mm). 14 — Paramere, lateral view. (Scale = 0,5 mm). 15 — Female, genital plates. (Scale = 1 mm)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/222978/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="401">
Figs. 
<number box="[276,348,1267,1291]" pageId="6" pageNumber="401" value="12.0" valueMax="13.0" valueMin="11.0">11–13</number>
</figureCitation>
). Ventral rim with lobes not reaching level of posterolateral angle (
<figureCitation box="[1098,1181,1266,1291]" captionStart="FIGURES 11 – 15" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1858,1881]" captionTargetBox="[169,1410,374,1826]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[159,1427,373,1837]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 11 – 15. Paraedessa albomaculata sp. nov. 11 – 13 Male, pygophore; 6 — dorsal view; 7 — posterior view; 8 — ventral view. (Scale = 1 mm). 14 — Paramere, lateral view. (Scale = 0,5 mm). 15 — Female, genital plates. (Scale = 1 mm)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/222978/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="401">
Fig. 
<number box="[1150,1181,1267,1291]" pageId="6" pageNumber="401" value="13.0">13</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,762,1615]" pageId="6" pageNumber="401">
Female: Gonocoxites 
<number box="[447,461,1303,1327]" pageId="6" pageNumber="401" value="8.0">8</number>
narrow, with sinuous distal margin, medially separated; posterolateral angle projected and dentiform, reaching or surpassing posterior margin of gonapophyses 
<number box="[992,1006,1339,1363]" pageId="6" pageNumber="401" value="8.0">8</number>
(
<figureCitation box="[1024,1110,1338,1363]" captionStart="FIGURES 11 – 15" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1858,1881]" captionTargetBox="[169,1410,374,1826]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[159,1427,373,1837]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 11 – 15. Paraedessa albomaculata sp. nov. 11 – 13 Male, pygophore; 6 — dorsal view; 7 — posterior view; 8 — ventral view. (Scale = 1 mm). 14 — Paramere, lateral view. (Scale = 0,5 mm). 15 — Female, genital plates. (Scale = 1 mm)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/222978/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="401">
Fig. 
<number box="[1079,1110,1338,1363]" pageId="6" pageNumber="401" value="15.0">15</number>
</figureCitation>
); gonocoxites 
<number box="[1279,1293,1339,1363]" pageId="6" pageNumber="401" value="8.0">8</number>
overlapping gonapophyses 
<number box="[317,331,1375,1399]" pageId="6" pageNumber="401" value="8.0">8</number>
for most of its length.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="401" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,762,1615]" pageId="6" pageNumber="401">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,335,1410,1435]" pageId="6" pageNumber="401">Comments.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[343,636,1410,1435]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Paraedessa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="401" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albomaculata" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[343,636,1410,1435]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="401">Paraedessa albomaculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[644,735,1410,1435]" pageId="6" pageNumber="401" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[644,735,1410,1435]" pageId="6" pageNumber="401">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
is recognized by the cordiform shape of the lateral expansion of proctiger; genital cup processes triangular and long; the shape of gonocoxites 
<number box="[1053,1069,1447,1471]" pageId="6" pageNumber="401" value="8.0">8</number>
. This species and 
<taxonomicName box="[1272,1377,1446,1471]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Paraedessa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="401" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="stolida">
<emphasis box="[1272,1377,1446,1471]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="401">P. stolida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have very similar gonocoxites 
<number box="[443,459,1483,1507]" pageId="6" pageNumber="401" value="8.0">8</number>
, but in 
<taxonomicName box="[551,735,1482,1507]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Paraedessa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="401" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albomaculata">
<emphasis box="[551,735,1482,1507]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="401">P. albomaculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
they are wider and the angle is rounded instead of acute (
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Paraedessa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="401" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="stolida">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="401">P. stolida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), and reaches or surpasses the distal margin of gonapophyses 
<number box="[923,939,1519,1543]" pageId="6" pageNumber="401" value="8.0">8</number>
. This species and 
<taxonomicName box="[1144,1266,1518,1543]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Paraedessa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="401" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="silvicola" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1144,1266,1518,1543]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="401">P. silvicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1273,1363,1518,1543]" pageId="6" pageNumber="401" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1273,1363,1518,1543]" pageId="6" pageNumber="401">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
, share the distal margin of parameres sloping and distal part of the paramere truncate and curved.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
